What is a disk image?
A disk image is a bit by bit copy of a hard drive.

What is the command to make a disk image?

What is a disk partition?
A part of a hard drive set aside for a specific purpose

How many partitions are in a disk image?
Depends, but usually the number is about 3-4 partitions on any one hard drive.

What difficulties does this pose if any?
You can only put one partition on a disk image.

What steps must you take to work with this?
You have to analyze the stopping and starting points of a hard drive to understand exactly where the partitions are.
